3
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:47,439
‐ [Girl] Roast Beef
of Lost Technology.

4
00:01:51,403 --> 00:01:53,153
‐ What’s your feeling
on this Forte?

5
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,530
Do you think it’s
possible that we’re

6
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:57,245
gonna find the lost
technology this time?

7
00:01:57,326 --> 00:01:59,366
‐ Oh I don’t know
and I’m not sure we

8
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:01,453
can rely too much on
what Colonel Volcott

9
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:03,118
has to say about it.

10
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:04,366
‐ Excuse me, Ranpha?

11
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:05,578
‐ Yeah what is it?

12
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,167
‐ I need your help.

13
00:02:07,294 --> 00:02:09,424
I can’t seem to find
the key to the gym room.

14
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:10,264
‐ [Ranpha] You don’t need it.

15
00:02:10,339 --> 00:02:11,799
I left it open.

16
00:02:11,882 --> 00:02:12,722
‐ Really?

17
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:13,929
That’s great!

18
00:02:14,009 --> 00:02:14,839
‐ [Ranpha] You’re
free to use the room,

19
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:16,548
but don’t make a mess okay?

20
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:21,467
‐ I’ll do my best.

21
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:23,138
‐ What was that all about?

22
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:26,148
‐ She wants to exercise to
get herself into better shape.

23
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:27,359
I mean, she’s been
going on about

24
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:28,691
how her uniform was starting to

25
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,725
feel and look tighter
around her waist.

26
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:33,652
And that’s no
surprise considering

27
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:35,409
how many sweets she eats.

28
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:37,029
‐ Well you’re one to talk.

29
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:38,117
You know, you’ve been looking a

30
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,290
little pudgy yourself lately.

31
00:02:40,369 --> 00:02:41,449
(girl yells)

32
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:43,116
‐ What are you talking about?

33
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:44,335
Pudgy?

34
00:02:44,456 --> 00:02:46,706
I’m 161 centimeters
tall and 43 kilos.

35
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,963
That’s just right
for me, just perfect.

36
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:52,214
‐ Oh Lord, please save
these wretched souls.

37
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:54,089
‐ What did you say Vanilla?

38
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:55,514
‐ Ranpha look, you’ve
got a meat bun.

39
00:02:55,634 --> 00:02:57,724
‐ What are you talking about?

40
00:02:57,844 --> 00:02:58,974
This isn’t a meat bun,

41
00:02:59,054 --> 00:03:01,184
it’s an imitation
bun, not a real one.

42
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:04,851
‐ Brigade, I think I’m
beginning to see it.

43
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:09,190
‐ [Robot] I see.

44
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:10,824
We didn’t discover it ’til now

45
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:13,189
because it was hidden above
these smaller planets.

46
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,026
‐ [Ranpha] It’s
really a ghost ship.

47
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:22,663
‐ That’s strange.

48
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,914
There are no hatches anywhere.

49
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,960
‐ [Robot] That light, and
there’s no mistaking it.

50
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:32,093
This spaceship was
definitely created

51
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:34,382
using the lost technology.

52
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:39,929
‐ [Ranpha] Looks
like the entrance.

53
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:40,893
Should we go in?

54
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:45,889
(robot yelling)

55
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:48,097
‐ Well it looks
safe enough to me.

56
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,058
Let’s go.

57
00:03:52,107 --> 00:03:55,147
‐ [Robot] My memory’s
been shaken up and fried.

58
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:56,105
‐ Oh no!

59
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,316
The entrance!

60
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:58,534
‐ It’s closed.

61
00:03:58,613 --> 00:03:59,453
‐ Duh!

62
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:00,413
As if I didn’t know that!

63
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:01,240
‐ Oh relax.

64
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:02,156
Don’t worry.

65
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,702
We’ve got lots of air.

66
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:06,575
Let’s just figure this out,
and if worst comes to worst,

67
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:08,253
we can use this
ultra miniature bomb

68
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:11,211
to blow the spaceship
to smithereens.

69
00:04:11,293 --> 00:04:12,753
‐ But if you use that bomb,

70
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:14,746
we’ll be blown to bits too.

71
00:04:14,838 --> 00:04:16,258
‐ [Forte] Boy, you’re no fun.

72
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:20,342
(ghost laughing)

73
00:04:20,427 --> 00:04:21,587
(girls screaming)

74
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,548
‐ What was that, what
was that, what was that?

75
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:26,348
‐ Wait, I think we forgot Forte!

76
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,393
‐ [Girl] Forte,
we’ll make sure that

77
00:04:28,477 --> 00:04:30,937
your death was not in vain.

78
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:33,232
‐ Were those proper respects?

79
00:04:33,315 --> 00:04:34,865
‐ No, not even close!

80
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,281
(girls yelling)

81
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,152
‐ Get out evil spirit,
get out evil spirit,

82
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,199
get out evil spirit!

83
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:44,081
I’ll give you all
the money you want!

84
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:45,869
‐ Hey, do you think
he’ll take a credit card?

85
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:46,702
‐ [Ranpha] No!

86
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:47,617
(girl screaming)

87
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:49,294
‐ Don’t worry Ranpha.

88
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:52,882
I’ll be just as happy when
you’re gone and forgotten.

89
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:53,789
‐ [Ranpha] Out of the way!

90
00:04:53,919 --> 00:04:56,049
Get out of the way!

91
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:58,379
(girls yelling)

92
00:04:58,465 --> 00:05:01,265
‐ There are more of them!

93
00:05:01,343 --> 00:05:03,183
Maybe we’ll just
blow them all up.

94
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,973
‐ I thought I told you already,

95
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:06,966
if you use that, we’ll
all be obliterated.

96
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:08,678
‐ How do you suppose
we deal with this

97
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,639
ridiculously insane situation?

98
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:13,058
‐ You think I could answer an

99
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,316
impossible question like
that any better than you?

100
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,320
(girl gasps)

101
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:17,691
I dropped them!

102
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:20,780
‐ I will haunt you
forever Ranpha.

103
00:05:22,197 --> 00:05:24,777
‐ I’m sorry Vanilla, Mint.

104
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:28,366
I promise I’ll overcome my
dislike for stinky soybeans

105
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:30,165
