fullest to make up

106
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:31,828
for how I’ve let you down.

107
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:35,707
‐ And you don’t like
pickled plum either, do you?

108
00:05:35,836 --> 00:05:38,246
‐ [Girls] Hey, let’s just
blow ourselves to bits.

109
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:42,009
(girls yelling)

110
00:05:45,554 --> 00:05:48,434
‐ It looks like we made it
and all still in one piece.

111
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:49,725
‐ Are we in heaven?

112
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:51,680
‐ If we are, I’ll
have one of those

113
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:54,310
heaven style spicy
bouillabaisses.

114
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:57,516
‐ [Robot] Hey,
there’s no such thing.

115
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:02,778
‐ Oh boy.

116
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:03,953
Looks like heaven to me.

117
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:06,200
‐ Then I want potato chips.

118
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:07,034
‐ Stew here.

119
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:08,198
‐ Stir fry.

120
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:13,872
‐ Boy, I sure can’t
get enough of this

121
00:06:13,999 --> 00:06:15,789
tasty stewed daikon radish.

122
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:17,036
‐ Yum.

123
00:06:17,127 --> 00:06:20,457
This spicy flavor sure
gets my appetite going.

124
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:22,257
‐ [Robot] How is it Vanilla?

125
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:23,632
‐ So how do you
think we’re going

126
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:25,927
to escape from this
spaceship you guys?

127
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,052
‐ [Girls] You mean
we’re not in heaven?

128
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:29,928
‐ [Mint] You really
thought we were?

129
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,733
(girls screaming)

130
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:40,228
‐ I’ve got some
good news Milfeulle.

131
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:41,397
‐ Wait!

132
00:06:41,526 --> 00:06:42,566
You’re going to
tell me how well I’m

133
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:44,074
doing with my fitness
program, right?

134
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:45,235
‐ [Man] No.

135
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:46,453
I’ve come to inform
you that your

136
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,663
probationary period
is finally over.

137
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:50,032
‐ Really?

138
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:51,538
‐ Yes.

139
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:53,330
I’ve just now received the
word from headquarters.

140
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:55,923
There will be an official
announcement shortly.

141
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:57,209
‐ Alright!

142
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:59,252
This means that today
I’m part of the team

143
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:02,087
that will fight for justice!

144
00:07:02,213 --> 00:07:04,013
‐ There’s more to it than that.

145
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,510
‐ There is?

146
00:07:05,592 --> 00:07:07,012
‐ Please help me!

147
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,143
‐ I can’t take this!

148
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:09,641
I can’t take this!

149
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:12,473
‐ And because of this, we
request an emergency rescue.

150
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:15,387
‐ Listen Volcott,
they’re calling for help.

151
00:07:15,477 --> 00:07:18,147
If I’m on the team now,
then I should deploy.

152
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:19,481
‐ Alright then.

153
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:21,766
Let’s just say that
you are now deployed.

154
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:22,938
‐ Alright!

155
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:24,108
‐ And Milfeulle.

156
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:25,065
‐ Yes?

157
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,613
‐ This means that you are now an

158
00:07:26,738 --> 00:07:29,278
official member of the
Galaxy Angel Brigade.

159
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:31,196
Do your very best.

160
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,124
‐ Yes.

161
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,873
I promise to give it my all.

162
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:35,964
(upbeat music)

163
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:39,291
(sirens blaring)

164
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:41,286
‐ Lost technology’s mysterious.

165
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:43,298
I can’t be sure
what will happen.

166
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:45,721
You must be very, very careful.

167
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:46,629
‐ Roger that.

168
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:50,392
Now lucky star, begin
deployment immediately

169
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,810
for the Angel Brigade
rescue mission.

170
00:07:52,931 --> 00:07:55,481
(upbeat music)

171
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:57,982
‐ [Milfeulle Voiceover]
I don’t know how this is

172
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,153
going to turn out,

