00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:01,400
but hang in there Angels
’til I get to you.

174
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:08,744
‐ Hey.

175
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:10,952
There’s a meat bun
flying around up here.

176
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:12,162
‐ Oh come on now Forte.

177
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:13,833
Can’t you see,
that’s no meat bun.

178
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:15,660
That’s a fake meat
bun that just happens

179
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:17,955
to look like a real
meat bun, you see.

180
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:19,329
‐ Oh it is?

181
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,667
Well now I’m thinking,

182
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,590
maybe it’s really
a bean bun that’s

183
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:24,709
pretending to be a meat bun.

184
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:27,628
‐ [Robot] They sure
seem to be having fun.

185
00:08:27,716 --> 00:08:30,466
(girls giggling)

186
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:33,514
‐ What do you think
this could be?

187
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,519
‐ [Robot] It looks like
some numbers to me.

188
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:38,679
‐ You don’t really know, do you?

189
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:41,440
‐ [Robot] How dare you
suggest that I don’t know?

190
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:45,321
I swear by my 10,000
gigahertz CPU that this.

191
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,534
‐ What is that?

192
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:50,362
It looks like an
image on the outside.

193
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:51,857
That’s one of ours.

194
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:52,738
It’s Milfeulle.

195
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:54,406
She’s come to rescue us.

196
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,369
‐ I don’t like this!

197
00:08:57,454 --> 00:08:58,624
Somebody help!

198
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:00,585
‐ Calm yourself down Milfeulle.

199
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:01,787
(girl yelling)

200
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,795
According to data we’ve
received from Forte,

201
00:09:03,877 --> 00:09:05,247
it seems that the
spaceship has the

202
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:07,258
power to read
people’s intentions.

203
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,880
It’s my guess that
the spaceship has

204
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:10,797
intercepted your
thoughts and is now

205
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:13,514
acting to interfere
with the rescue mission.

206
00:09:13,595 --> 00:09:15,055
‐ Well okay then.

207
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:16,760
I know!

208
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:24,312
‐ [Robot] Now what are those?

209
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:27,067
‐ Those meat buns
are scary looking.

210
00:09:27,192 --> 00:09:28,362
‐ What are you talking about?

211
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:30,903
Those aren’t spicy
meat buns at all!

212
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:41,582
‐ I’m sorry for taking so long.

213
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:42,504
Look!

214
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:43,752
I brought you some apple pie.

215
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:46,135
‐ Now look you, what
are you doing here?

216
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,752
‐ What are you saying Ranpha?

217
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:49,759
I thought you liked apple pie.

218
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:52,129
‐ Why are you always
pulling this cute act

219
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:55,258
and trying to make yourself out
to be some kind of big star?

220
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:56,756
‐ [Milfeulle] What do you mean?

221
00:09:56,846 --> 00:09:59,266
‐ [Robot] You think we should
just let them have it out?

222
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,810
‐ [Mint] I think we
should be thinking about

223
00:10:00,934 --> 00:10:03,064
how we’re going to
get out of this place.

224
00:10:05,355 --> 00:10:06,735
It looks like another column of

225
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:08,865
numbers is showing
on this monitor.

226
00:10:10,819 --> 00:10:13,109
And they’re getting bigger too.

227
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:15,315
‐ [Ranpha] How’s this?

228
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:16,868
And that?

229
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:19,290
‐ Now Ranpha, you know if
you keep eating like that,

230
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,330
you’re going to turn into a pig.

231
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:22,584
‐ [Robot] Or a cow maybe.

232
00:10:22,664 --> 00:10:23,914
(girl yells)

233
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,628
‐ Ranpha’s turning into a pig!

234
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,500
‐ Now they’ve stopped.

235
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,797
‐ [Ranpha] I’m gonna get you!

236
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:31,169
And you.

237
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:35,177
‐ Now they’re going back up.
‐ And get you again!

238
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,641
‐ [Robot] My 10,000
gigahertz CPU!

239
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,470
‐ Now they’ve stopped.

240
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:43,429
And now they’re going up again.

241
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,312
Could this possibly mean?

242
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:50,824
(clock ticking)

243
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,490
I’ve got it!

244
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:54,029
‐ Hey, wait a minute.

245
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:56,914
This number is my
exact desired weight.

246
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:58,240
I’ve got an idea.

247
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,584
Do you think this
spaceship could

248
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:01,079
actually be some kind of giant

249
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:03,501
diet, fitness, and
training machine?

250
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:06,331
‐ My moment of brilliant
realization ruined.

251
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:07,327
‐ What?

252
00:11:07,417 --> 00:11:08,577
Then are you saying that those

253
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,628
ghost monsters were
only chasing us around

254
00:11:10,712 --> 00:11:13,712
to make us run and exercise
so much that we’d lose wight?

255
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,920
Now I get it!

256
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,508
(girl laughs)

257
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:18,434
Wait a minute!

258
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:19,641
Are you trying to tell us that

